This is SAC Communications Control.

953
01:10:45,576 --> 01:10:47,168
Over and out.

954
01:10:47,239 --> 01:10:49,061
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

955
01:10:49,126 --> 01:10:51,428
Gentlemen.

956
01:10:51,495 --> 01:10:53,350
Mr. President.

957
01:10:53,415 --> 01:10:55,423
I'm not a sentimentalist by nature...

958
01:10:55,495 --> 01:10:58,626
but I think I know what's
in every heart in this room.

959
01:10:58,695 --> 01:11:02,373
I think we all ought
to bow our heads...

960
01:11:02,440 --> 01:11:04,416
and give a prayer of thanks
for our deliverance.

961
01:11:04,488 --> 01:11:05,863
Lord...

962
01:11:07,049 --> 01:11:11,457
we have heard the wings
of the Angel of Death...

963
01:11:11,529 --> 01:11:14,278
fluttering over our heads
from the Valley of Fear.

964
01:11:14,343 --> 01:11:16,896
You have seen fit to deliver us
from the forces of evil...

965
01:11:16,967 --> 01:11:18,495
Excuse me, sir.

966
01:11:18,569 --> 01:11:21,569
Premier Kissoff's calling again
and he's hopping mad.

967
01:11:28,041 --> 01:11:31,816
Fuel flow on active engines
and leakage has increased.

968
01:11:31,882 --> 01:11:35,744
Now works out at 2-0-5.

969
01:11:36,778 --> 01:11:38,687
Estimate remaining fuel...

970
01:11:38,761 --> 01:11:42,503
at 8-7-9-0.

971
01:11:45,705 --> 01:11:49,416
Roger.
Confirm 2-0-5 per minute...

972
01:11:49,482 --> 01:11:53,377
and remaining fuel 8-7-9-0.

973
01:11:59,626 --> 01:12:03,556
No, no, Dimitri,
there must be some mistake.

974
01:12:03,628 --> 01:12:05,600
No, I'm certain of that.

975
01:12:05,673 --> 01:12:09,700
I'm perfectly certain
of that, Dimitri.

976
01:12:09,770 --> 01:12:12,552
Just a second.
You know what he says?

977
01:12:12,618 --> 01:12:14,789
He says one of the planes
hasn't turned back.

978
01:12:14,859 --> 01:12:17,347
He says according to information
forwarded by our A ir Staffs...

979
01:12:17,419 --> 01:12:20,234
it's headed for
the missile complex at Laputa.

980
01:12:23,114 --> 01:12:25,930
That's impossible, Mr. President.

981
01:12:25,995 --> 01:12:27,970
I mean, look at the big board.

982
01:12:28,044 --> 01:12:31,045
Thirty-four planes, 30 recalls
acknowledged and four splashes...

983
01:12:31,117 --> 01:12:33,865
and one of them
was targeted for Laputa.

984
01:12:36,684 --> 01:12:39,750
Dimitri, look, we've got
an acknowledgement from every plane...

985
01:12:39,820 --> 01:12:42,951
except the four you've shot down.

986
01:12:49,997 --> 01:12:52,298
Hang on a second, Dimitri.

987
01:12:52,365 --> 01:12:55,561
He says their air defense now only
claims three aircraft confirmed.

988
01:12:55,629 --> 01:12:57,996
The fourth may only be damaged.

989
01:13:00,076 --> 01:13:01,931
Mr. President...

990
01:13:01,996 --> 01:13:04,266
I'm beginning to smell
a big, fat Commie rat.

991
01:13:04,332 --> 01:13:08,042
I mean, supposing Kissoff is lying
about that fourth plane...

992
01:13:08,108 --> 01:13:10,182
just looking for
an excuse to clobber us?

993
01:13:10,253 --> 01:13:12,587
If the spaghetti hits the fan,
we're in trouble.

994
01:13:16,525 --> 01:13:19,013
Dimitri, look,
if this report is true...

995
01:13:19,085 --> 01:13:22,565
and the plane manages
to bomb the target...

996
01:13:22,638 --> 01:13:26,695
is this gonna set off
the doomsday machine?

997
01:13:29,805 --> 01:13:31,692
Are you sure?

998
01:13:32,845 --> 01:13:37,221
Well, I guess you're just gonna have
to get that plane, Dimitri.

999
01:13:37,294 --> 01:13:40,229
I'm sorry they're jamming
your radar and flying so low...

1000
01:13:40,303 --> 01:13:42,408
but they're trained to do it.

1001
01:13:42,478 --> 01:13:44,072
It's initiative.

1002
01:13:45,711 --> 01:13:48,461
Look, Dimitri, you know
exactly where they're going...

1003
01:13:48,527 --> 01:13:51,559
and I'm sure your entire air defense
can stop a single plane.

1004
01:13:54,606 --> 01:13:59,013
It's not gonna help either one of us
if the doomsday machine goes off, is it?

1005
01:14:00,494 --> 01:14:05,546
There's no point in you getting
hysterical at a moment like this!

1006
01:14:05,615 --> 01:14:09,675
Keep your feet on the ground
when you're talking, Dimitri.

1007
01:14:09,744 --> 01:14:11,915
I am not...
I am not getting...

1008
01:14:11,984 --> 01:14:14,319
No, Dimitri, I'm just worried.

1009
01:14:14,384 --> 01:14:16,206
That's all.

1010
01:14:16,272 --> 01:14:19,206
Now look, if our A ir Staffs say
its primary target is Laputa...

1011
01:14:19,279 --> 01:14:23,075
and its secondary target is Borchov,
it's true.

1012
01:14:23,152 --> 01:14:24,526
You gotta believe it!

1013
01:14:24,590 --> 01:14:28,170
Dimitri, can I give you
just one word...

1014
01:14:28,240 --> 01:14:31,436
Can I give you just one word
of advice, Dimitri?

1015
01:14:31,505 --> 01:14:33,097
Listen, Dimitri.

1016
01:14:33,168 --> 01:14:36,583
Put everything you've got into
those two sectors, and you can't miss!

1017
01:14:42,706 --> 01:14:46,218
Sir, if we continue to lose fuel
at the present rate...

1018
01:14:46,289 --> 01:14:50,249
I estimate we only have
38 minutes flying time...

1019
01:14:50,320 --> 01:14:52,688
which will not even take us
as far as the primary.

1020
01:14:52,753 --> 01:14:56,528
Doggone it, Sweets, you told me that
you could get me to the primary!

1021
01:14:56,593 --> 01:15:00,271
I'm sorry, sir. That estimate was based
on the original loss rate factor...

1022
01:15:00,338 --> 01:15:02,061
not at 2-0-5.

1023
01:15:02,129 --> 01:15:04,301
I don't give a hoot in hell
how you do it...

1024
01:15:04,370 --> 01:15:06,443
you just get me to
the primary, you hear?

1025
01:15:06,514 --> 01:15:09,810
I'm sorry, sir,
but those are the figures.

1026
01:15:09,875 --> 01:15:13,004
We'll be lucky to reach
weather ship at Tango Delta.

1027
01:15:13,073 --> 01:15:15,178
Well, shoot!

1028
01:15:15,248 --> 01:15:19,406
We ain't come this far just
to dump this thing in the drink.

1029
01:15:19,473 --> 01:15:21,383
What's the nearest
target of opportunity?

1030
01:15:29,810 --> 01:15:32,429
Sir, if the rate of loss
does not increase...

1031
01:15:32,499 --> 01:15:36,112
we have a chance
to reach target 3-8-4...

1032
01:15:36,180 --> 01:15:40,815
grid coordinate 0-0-3-6-9-1...

1033
01:15:40,882 --> 01:15:44,592
and possibly make it from there
to the Tango Delta weather ship.

1034
01:15:44,658 --> 01:15:46,698
What kind of a target
is that, anyhow?

1035
01:15:46,771 --> 01:15:50,547
Sir, that's the I.C.B.M.
complex at Kotloss.

1036
01:15:50,612 --> 01:15:56,111
Alright.
Designating new target: 3-8-4.

1037
01:15:56,179 --> 01:15:59,049
Give me a head-iron that just as soon
as you get it worked out.

1038
01:16:10,738 --> 01:16:15,409
We'll keep our fingers crossed.
Remember, we're all in this together.

1039
01:16:15,476 --> 01:16:19,153
We're right behind you,
we're with you all the way.

1040
01:16:19,220 --> 01:16:22,798
Yes. We'll keep the line open.

1041
01:16:22,868 --> 01:16:24,242
Alright, Dimitri.

1042
01:16:26,516 --> 01:16:27,891
General Turgidson...

1043
01:16:27,958 --> 01:16:31,055
is there really a chance
for that plane to get through?

1044
01:16:32,692 --> 01:16:35,026
Mr. President,
if I may speak freely.

1045
01:16:35,093 --> 01:16:38,573
The Ruskie talks big, but frankly
we think he's short of know-how.

1046
01:16:38,645 --> 01:16:42,955
You can't expect ignorant peons
to understand a machine like our boys.

1047
01:16:43,029 --> 01:16:45,363
That's not meant as an insult,
Mr. Ambassador.

1048
01:16:45,430 --> 01:16:47,917
We all know how much guts
the average Ruskie's got.

1049
01:16:47,989 --> 01:16:50,990
Look at all of them Nazis killed
off, and they still wouldn't quit!

1050
01:16:51,062 --> 01:16:52,885
Can't you stick to the point?

1051
01:16:52,951 --> 01:16:56,529
Well, sir,
if the pilot's good, see...

1052
01:16:56,599 --> 01:17:00,591
I mean, if he's really sharp,
he can barrel that baby in so low.

1053
01:17:00,661 --> 01:17:04,971
You oughta see it! It's a sight!
A big plane like a 52! Vroom!

1054
01:17:05,045 --> 01:17:07,980
Its jet exhaust frying chickens
in the barnyard!

1055
01:17:08,053 --> 01:17:11,054
- But has he got a chance?
- Has he got a chance?

1056
01:17:11,126 --> 01:17:12,501
Hell, ye...

